race.description: John Duff & Co Vobis Gold Bullion
race.comment: PERSIAN SPIRIT (7) looks the one to beat. His win two back at Flemington was awesome in very fast time, ripping home down the outside to win by 4.5 lengths. He just got shuffled back at a key stage at Caulfield and flew home but couldn't reel in Here To Shock who was ridden to perfection out in front. He was clearly the fastest home and they gapped the rest, now he comes back in grade and gets in well with 55.5kg. NDOLA (10) is the danger and not hopeless of knocking him off. PERSIAN SPIRIT did thump him at Flemington but NDOLA started $4.40 vs $4.80 there and now meets him 7kg better off. REGAL ZEUS (2) was given a picnic in front and won the Kilmore Cup easily last time. Back to 1400m is a little niggle here but he'll take catching. RUN HARRY RUN (5) won well fresh and drops 5kg with improvement to come.
